    front: 'What is configuration drift and how does it relate to change management?',
    back: 'Configuration drift: the gradual divergence of a system\'s actual configuration from its documented baseline — caused by untracked changes, manual fixes, software updates, or ad-hoc adjustments.\n\nWhy it\'s a problem:\n- Systems behave differently than expected based on documentation\n- Security vulnerabilities introduced by undocumented changes go undetected\n- Troubleshooting is harder because assumptions about configuration are wrong\n- Compliance audits fail when actual state differs from documented state\n\nPrevention:\n- Enforce change management — all changes require an RFC\n- Use configuration management tools (Ansible, Puppet, Chef) that enforce desired state\n- Regular configuration audits compare current state to baseline\n- Immutable infrastructure (rebuild from code rather than patch in place)',
