    back: 'Hot site: fully equipped and operational duplicate of the primary data center. Systems are running, data is synchronized in near-real-time. Failover can occur in minutes.\n- Cost: highest (paying for duplicate running infrastructure)\n- RTO: very low (minutes to hours)\n\nWarm site: facility with hardware installed and configured but not running. Data must be restored from backups. Requires hours to days to bring online.\n- Cost: medium (hardware cost but no ongoing compute cost)\n- RTO: hours to days\n\nCold site: a physical space with power, cooling, and connectivity but no hardware. Equipment must be sourced and installed before recovery can begin.\n- Cost: lowest\n- RTO: days to weeks\n\nChoice is driven by RTO requirements and budget.',
